<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 20px;
            color: #333;
        }
        .header {
            border-bottom: 2px solid #007acc;
            padding-bottom: 10px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        .content {
            margin: 20px 0;
        }
        .meta {
            background: #f5f5f5;
            padding: 10px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            font-size: 0.9em;
            color: #666;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="header">
        <h1><%= title %></h1>
        <p>A simple, semantic HTML page for basic testing</p>
    </div>

    <div class="content">
        <h2>About This Page</h2>
        <p>This is a simple HTML page designed for testing basic web-to-PDF conversion functionality. It contains semantic HTML elements and predictable content.</p>
        
        <h3>Features</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Clean, semantic HTML structure</li>
            <li>Predictable title for filename generation</li>
            <li>Standard typography and spacing</li>
            <li>Basic CSS styling</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Testing Scenarios</h3>
        <p>This page is ideal for testing:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Basic PDF generation</li>
            <li>Title-based filename generation</li>
            <li>Font rendering and typography</li>
            <li>CSS styling preservation</li>
        </ol>

        <blockquote>
            <p>"The best way to test web-to-PDF conversion is with clean, predictable content."</p>
        </blockquote>
    </div>

    <div class="meta">
        <p><strong>Generated:</strong> <%= timestamp %></p>
        <p><strong>Page Type:</strong> Simple Static Content</p>
        <p><strong>Test Category:</strong> Basic Layout</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>